<exercise checkit-seed="0004" checkit-slug="TI4" checkit-title="Trigonometric Substitution">
    <statement>
        <p>
Find the appropriate trignometric substitution for <m>x</m> and rewrite <me>\int \sqrt{x^{2} + 1} dx</me> as an integral in terms of <m>\theta</m>.
        </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        We substitute <m>x=\tan\left(\theta\right).</m>  Then <m>dx=\sec\left(\theta\right)d\theta</m> and:
        <me>
\int \sqrt{x^{2} + 1} dx = \int \sqrt{\tan\left(\theta\right)^{2} + 1} \sec\left(\theta\right) d\theta = \int \sqrt{\sec\left(\theta\right)^{2}} \sec\left(\theta\right) d\theta.
        </me>
    </answer>
</exercise>
